  "prompt": "Are there laws that prevent the disguise of illicit funds?",
  "response": "Yes, there are anti-money laundering (AML) laws and regulations in many countries designed to prevent the disguise or concealment of illicit funds. Some key examples include:\n\n1. Bank Secrecy Act (US)\n2. Anti-Money Laundering Act\n3. Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n4. Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n5. Proceeds of Crime laws\n\nThese laws require financial institutions to:\n- Verify customer identities\n- Report suspicious transactions\n- Maintain transaction records\n- Conduct due diligence on financial activities\n\nViolations can result in significant legal penalties and criminal prosecution.",
